title: sephanyR
author: sephanyR
content: Hello I just found inside my brother old PC a wallet with 663 USDT this is a picture of the wallet https://i.ibb.co/nCbKQBp/ss.jpgHow can I convert it to real $ any one can help me I will give him 30$this is the key I found inside text file :ill segment circle key record distance pretty follow lecture lift goose over

comments.author: serjent05
comments.body: You can follow this tutorial on how to sell USDT on Binance P2P https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=39b0OxkvOxQHere is the process.If you don't have an account on Binance, then better open an account to binance and have it verified.The site: https://binance.com/Then you can transfer your USDT to binance just make sure that the deposit address is TRC20you can follow this steps https://thefipharmacist.com/deposit-trc20-tokens-on-binance/It will take you some time if you don't have a verified account on Binance yet.But I think it would be better to ask your brother about your problem.  I think he will be willing to tell you the process of converting that USDT to cash

comments.body: OP, You look scammy to me. Your previous post you showed your nodes collection which obviously requires more complex understanding than just securing seed phrases, and now you are like a fool sharing a phrase asking for help cashing out your brother's wallet?By the way, where did you get the "total nodes value" from?

comments.author: Detritus
comments.body: This is scam, I have come across lot of scammers sharing wallet key and asking people to help them trade the token in the wallet. But once you send gas to the adress, you won't be able to send out the token and your gas is going to be send out by unknown person.Even a dummy can not come public and post a wallet private key knowing full well it's what can give any one access to their funds.

comments.author: klarki
comments.body: Only a very inattentive user would fall for a scammer.I recommend reading this article: https://community.trustwallet.com/t/trust-wallet-adds-a-scam-prevention-update-aimed-at-tron-multi-sig-scams/534456

comments.author: Bitcoin_Arena
comments.body: Trying to pull-off a tron multi-signature wallet scam. Nice try, but no quite  Those who are not aware of the scam OP is trying to pull of, please read here - [Warning] Trust wallet tron multi signature scam

comments.author: Bananington
comments.body: Quote from: Bitcoin_Arena on September 12, 2022, 11:57:15 PMTrying to pull-off a tron multi-signature wallet scam. Nice try, but no quite  Very sketchy, OP even made it look less obvious by trying to reduce the reward amount so it doesn't look ridiculous. Newbies who have never been victims or heard people's experience of this sort of scam will think to themselves that there is no harm in trying to help this person to claim this easy reward and would have fallen for this. It is a good thing that people here are aware of this tron multi-signature wallet scam.
